If enabled, you should see it in your startup messages:
if you connect via a websocket (on $http/port +1, e.g. 81), you have a
streaming connection to FluidNC that behaves just like serial. You send
newline-delimited lines just like you would over serial, and get back the same
ok or error responses. Flow control is the same as for serial, as documented
on the plain old Grbl wiki.
You can use xmodem via serial port to upload ﬁles to the localfs. This can be
helpful to upload conﬁg ﬁles. you must be in the Idle or Alarm states.
